-- Hasbro plans facility overhaul, job cuts
-- 
-- Wed Jan 9, 2008 1:26pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/09/us-hasbro-plan-idUSWNAS603020080109

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Hasbro Inc HAS.N, the world's second-largest toy and game company, announced plans to improve productivity at its Massachusetts facility on Wednesday, a move that will cut 200 jobs. 

 The company said it will invest about $40 million, including $10 million right away to overhaul its equipment. (Reporting by  Aarthi Sivaraman ; Editing by  Brian Moss )